-04-15T10:02:46.000Z","msg":"如題，學左一排都唔太明白skipcond 個定義係咩<img src=\"/assets/faces/cow/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n究竟點樣拎嚟整loop<br />\n有冇高手可以解釋吓<img src=\"/assets/faces/cow/sorry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-04-16T00:22:52.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://marie.js.org/book.pdf\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmarie.js.org%2Fbook.pdf&d=Uh5SjXth0XRRLWSKrhPNwA%2BnBs0jvEEXkL0KxwFTSeM%3D&h=b0bac63b\" target=\"_blank\">https://marie.js.org/book.pdf</a> <br />\n<br />\npage 4<br />\n<br />\nIn MARIE, each instruction is 16 bits long with the first 4 bits representing the opcode and the remaining 12 bits are being used to<br />\nrepresent the address.<br />\n<br />\npage 5<br />\nSkipcond (C) 8<br />\nSkips the next instruction based on C: if (C) is<br />\n- 000: Skips if AC &lt; 0<br />\n- 400: Skips if AC = 0<br />\n- 800: Skips if AC &gt; 0<br />\n<br />\nAssume instruction bits are order from left to right.  The following are 3 valid variants of the Skipcond instruction.<br />\n<br />\n8000: Skip if AC &lt; 0<br />\n8400: Skip if AC = 0<br />\n8800: Skip if AC &gt; 0"},{"pid":"9c9bd9e60c3c1129f1741e4aa698ab1550f13df3","tid":2490032,"uid":105553,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"11e17aead609d5e07ffdf27912da74b50b5cd48a","tid":2490032,"uid":105553,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"602a924d10f345cf9a1c0200909e872de89450bd","tid":2490032,"uid":391215,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-04-15T10:02:46.000Z","msg":"如題，學左一排都唔太明白skipcond 個定義係咩<img src=\"/assets/faces/cow/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n究竟點樣拎嚟整loop<br />\n有冇高手可以解釋吓<img src=\"/assets/faces/cow/sorry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-04-16T00:22:52.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://marie.js.org/book.pdf\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmarie.js.org%2Fbook.pdf&d=Uh5SjXth0XRRLWSKrhPNwA%2BnBs0jvEEXkL0KxwFTSeM%3D&h=b0bac63b\" target=\"_blank\">https://marie.js.org/book.pdf</a> <br />\n<br />\npage 4<br />\n<br />\nIn MARIE, each instruction is 16 bits long with the first 4 bits representing the opcode and the remaining 12 bits are being used to<br />\nrepresent the address.<br />\n<br />\npage 5<br />\nSkipcond (C) 8<br />\nSkips the next instruction based on C: if (C) is<br />\n- 000: Skips if AC &lt; 0<br />\n- 400: Skips if AC = 0<br />\n- 800: Skips if AC &gt; 0<br />\n<br />\nAssume instruction bits are order from left to right.  The following are 3 valid variants of the Skipcond instruction.<br />\n<br />\n8000: Skip if AC &lt; 0<br />\n8400: Skip if AC = 0<br />\n8800: Skip if AC &gt; 0"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-04-16T04:35:08.000Z","msg":"skipcond 可以跳過下一個指令。至於點樣用黎做loop，諗下個loop body最後應該要做啲乜嘢。提示係咁多，功課自己做。"}]}